item.title: Four people including a police officer injured after car crash and stabbing in Sydney’s south
item.description:
NSW police called to two-vehicle crash at intersection of Princes Highway and Old Bush Road in Engadine

  • Follow our Australia news live blog for latest updates
  • Get our morning and afternoon news emails, free app or daily news podcast

Four people including a police officer have been injured following a car crash and stabbing in Sydney’s south, New South Wales police say.

Multiple calls were made to triple zero on Sunday morning after a two-vehicle crash at the intersection of the Princes Highway and Old Bush Road in Engadine at about 9am, police said in a statement.
